1
00:00:01,060 --> 00:00:12,240
♪

2
00:00:12,240 --> 00:00:15,150
♪ (singing in Japanese) ♪

3
00:00:15,150 --> 00:01:33,190
♪

4
00:01:35,052 --> 00:01:47,170
♪

5
00:01:47,170 --> 00:01:49,060
(laughing)

6
00:01:49,060 --> 00:01:51,100
Today's the day.

7
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:55,250
♪

8
00:01:55,250 --> 00:01:58,030
And now it's white.

9
00:01:58,030 --> 00:01:59,080
-So white!
-So white!

10
00:01:59,080 --> 00:02:01,050
(laughing)

11
00:02:01,050 --> 00:02:13,100
♪

12
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:15,270
Rise and shine!

13
00:02:15,270 --> 00:02:16,250
Let me sleep,

14
00:02:16,250 --> 00:02:18,030
I was up late drinking

15
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:20,120
and losing at dice.

16
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:21,120
Up.

17
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:22,130
Hey!

18
00:02:22,130 --> 00:02:25,020
You and your six
five sake binges.

19
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:27,220
Don't you remember
what today is, you lout?

20
00:02:27,220 --> 00:02:29,190
Yeah, today's May 14th.

21
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:30,260
Today's the day that Kenshin's

22
00:02:30,260 --> 00:02:33,100
supposed to give the
Okubo guy his big answer.

23
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:36,010
I just hope he doesn't
bring that Kawaji.

24
00:02:36,010 --> 00:02:38,020
Yeah, he's a real pompous jerk.

25
00:02:38,020 --> 00:02:39,030
Let's stop talking

26
00:02:39,030 --> 00:02:41,250
and go find Kenshin.

27
00:02:41,250 --> 00:02:47,020
♪

28
00:02:47,020 --> 00:02:51,220
Come on, let's try
to find some frogs.

29
00:02:51,220 --> 00:02:52,270
I see.

30
00:02:52,270 --> 00:02:54,210
And so today's the day, huh?

31
00:02:54,210 --> 00:02:56,280
We've let Kenshin know
we're here to help him.

32
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:58,020
No matter what kind of pressure

33
00:02:58,020 --> 00:02:59,170
Okubo puts on Kenshin

34
00:02:59,170 --> 00:03:01,280
we won't allow them
to force Kenshin to go.

35
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:04,100
So what does Kenshin
say about all this?

36
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:06,200
He's not going to go.

37
00:03:09,140 --> 00:03:11,040
♪

38
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:13,010
This is where we saw
them, right, Grandpa?

39
00:03:13,010 --> 00:03:14,110
Hm?

40
00:03:14,110 --> 00:03:17,030
This is the spot where we
see fireflies every year.

41
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:18,200
Where are they now?

42
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:19,210
By next week you'll see them.

43
00:03:19,210 --> 00:03:21,130
Fireflies.

44
00:03:21,130 --> 00:03:23,100
I guess I wasn't
here last summer.

45
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:25,260
Oh, they shine as
bright as a candle.

46
00:03:25,260 --> 00:03:28,000
They sure do.

47
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,210
So have you ever
seen them before?

48
00:03:29,210 --> 00:03:31,030
Mhmm.

49
00:03:31,030 --> 00:03:33,050
When they get here that's
where they'll see us.

50
00:03:33,050 --> 00:03:34,230
They'll shine for
me and you, too.

51
00:03:34,230 --> 00:03:35,290
They're shiny buggy bugs!

52
00:03:35,290 --> 00:03:38,010
Seems like Kenshin's
been here forever.

53
00:03:38,010 --> 00:03:40,020
Even though he's been
with us less than a year

54
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:42,200
he sure has become
a part of the family.

55
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:44,240
He is one of us and I love him.

56
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:46,020
And I'd do almost anything

57
00:03:46,020 --> 00:03:48,030
to keep him a
part of our family.

58
00:03:48,030 --> 00:03:51,230
Let's go find some frogs.

59
00:03:51,230 --> 00:03:54,090
Let's come back
here tonight, okay?

60
00:03:54,090 --> 00:03:55,731
For the fireflies?

61
00:03:55,731 --> 00:03:56,693
It'll be fun.

62
00:03:56,693 --> 00:03:58,030
Yes, and all of us will come.

63
00:03:58,030 --> 00:03:59,160
Yeah, promise, promise!

64
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:03,240
♪

65
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:05,260
Uh...

66
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:07,050
Hey!

67
00:04:07,050 --> 00:04:08,280
He can't make any
promises for tonight

68
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:11,000
until he tells Okubo no, right?

69
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,000
We all know you couldn't
possibly be stupid enough

70
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,230
to accept his crazy offer.

71
00:04:14,230 --> 00:04:15,270
I know you wanna help,

72
00:04:15,270 --> 00:04:17,220
but there's only
one logical choice.

73
00:04:17,220 --> 00:04:19,270
Yeah, those guys could
care less about you.

74
00:04:19,270 --> 00:04:22,120
All they want is to get
their dirty work done.

75
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,270
Okubo wants you to risk it all,

76
00:04:23,270 --> 00:04:25,130
and the Meiji
government is so rotten

77
00:04:25,130 --> 00:04:27,100
that it's sure not worth
putting your life on the line

78
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:28,170
for those jerks.

79
00:04:28,170 --> 00:04:30,090
Boy, you must really
hate the Meiji government

80
00:04:30,090 --> 00:04:32,240
to talk about it that way, Sano.

81
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:33,280
Wrong again!

82
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:35,230
It's not as black
and white as that.

83
00:04:35,230 --> 00:04:37,250
I'm sure Okubo was
really greedy or corrupt

84
00:04:37,250 --> 00:04:40,010
Saito would've already
killed him by now.

85
00:04:40,010 --> 00:04:42,140
That's why this
decision's so tough.

86
00:04:42,140 --> 00:04:43,230
Saito?

87
00:04:43,230 --> 00:04:45,160
Isn't he that phony policeman?

88
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:48,210
Slash evil now.

89
00:04:48,210 --> 00:04:50,180
The Shinsen group
and slashers of honor

90
00:04:50,180 --> 00:04:54,060
are the only protectors of
righteousness in our society.

91
00:04:54,060 --> 00:04:56,190
He still believes the
philosophy of idealizing

92
00:04:56,190 --> 00:04:57,240
what's truly right,

93
00:04:57,240 --> 00:05:00,020
even in this mixed up Meiji era.

94
00:05:00,020 --> 00:05:01,180
He acts like a lone wolf,

95
00:05:01,180 --> 00:05:03,190
defending justice and
protecting the righteous

96
00:05:03,190 --> 00:05:05,090
from evil.

97
00:05:05,090 --> 00:05:07,290
Of course, that doesn't mean
that it's any easier
to get along with him.

98
00:05:07,290 --> 00:05:08,200
You're right.

99
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:09,180
He's a real pain.

100
00:05:09,180 --> 00:05:10,200
-We hate him.
-We hate him.

101
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:11,220
-We hate him, too.
-We hate him, too.

102
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:13,180
-We hate him, too.
-We hate him, too.

103
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:16,150
(sneezing)

104
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:20,050
How crass.

105
00:05:20,050 --> 00:05:21,100
You are a pig.

106
00:05:21,100 --> 00:05:22,130
Why, thank you.

107
00:05:22,130 --> 00:05:23,140
Stupid people like you

108
00:05:23,140 --> 00:05:25,110
judge everyone by what you see.

109
00:05:25,110 --> 00:05:26,110
But so what?

110
00:05:26,110 --> 00:05:27,200
As a member of
the Shinsen Group

111
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:28,230
I'm used to being despised

112
00:05:28,230 --> 00:05:30,020
no matter what I do.

113
00:05:34,020 --> 00:05:37,100
Today's May 14th?

114
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:40,110
Battosai, today's
your decision day.

115
00:05:40,110 --> 00:05:42,100
If you'll excuse me.

116
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:43,170
Where are you going?

117
00:05:43,170 --> 00:05:44,220
Are you leaving?

118
00:05:44,220 --> 00:05:45,140
Mhmm.

119
00:05:45,140 --> 00:05:47,050
Kenshin?

120
00:05:47,050 --> 00:05:50,230
I need to go and
give Sir Okubo my answer.

121
00:05:50,230 --> 00:05:52,060
But wait a second.

122
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:53,280
He said he was
going to come here.

123
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:55,140
I'm sure he has
more important matters

124
00:05:55,140 --> 00:05:58,130
than to waste time
traveling here.

125
00:05:58,130 --> 00:06:04,010
It will also show
how much I respect him.

126
00:06:04,010 --> 00:06:06,220
You're not going to leave.

127
00:06:06,220 --> 00:06:08,270
Ahhhh!

128
00:06:08,270 --> 00:06:10,220
There's only one
way to keep a man,

129
00:06:10,220 --> 00:06:11,270
and that's to make sure he knows

130
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:13,050
just who's in control

131
00:06:13,050 --> 00:06:14,260
and keep him on a short leash.

132
00:06:14,260 --> 00:06:16,230
And I give him some
of my pleasure balm

133
00:06:16,230 --> 00:06:18,020
to keep him totally satisfied

134
00:06:18,020 --> 00:06:19,220
and help seduce him.

135
00:06:19,220 --> 00:06:21,030
(laughing)

136
00:06:21,030 --> 00:06:23,100
You stop that kind
of talk, Megumi.

137
00:06:23,100 --> 00:06:26,020
Women, they are scary.

138
00:06:26,020 --> 00:06:27,220
So just where can
I get some of that

139
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:29,130
for my lady friends?

140
00:06:29,130 --> 00:06:31,040
Oh, Dr. Gensai.

141
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:32,080
Really, now.

142
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:33,220
Thanks for the thought.

143
00:06:33,220 --> 00:06:35,180
But I really have
to get going now.

144
00:06:35,180 --> 00:06:36,270
But, Kenshin, how
can you expect to find

145
00:06:36,270 --> 00:06:39,170
just where Okubo is anyway?

146
00:06:39,170 --> 00:06:41,100
He mentioned that today
he would be visiting

147
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:44,220
the county administrator in
Akasaka so I'm walking there.

148
00:06:44,220 --> 00:06:46,200
If that's the situation
then we'll all go.

149
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:47,260
No.

150
00:06:47,260 --> 00:06:49,190
I think it's best
that I go there alone,

151
00:06:49,190 --> 00:06:53,270
it'll make things a lot easier.

152
00:06:53,270 --> 00:07:04,090
♪

153
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:06,130
Don't worry, Kaoru.

154
00:07:06,130 --> 00:07:08,080
Kenshin knows this
is where he belongs.

155
00:07:08,080 --> 00:07:10,170
When he's finished with his
business he'll come back.

156
00:07:10,170 --> 00:07:12,060
This dojo's his home.

157
00:07:12,060 --> 00:07:13,240
He'll be back tonight.

158
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:14,260
He's not gonna kill anybody

159
00:07:14,260 --> 00:07:16,030
for any government.

160
00:07:16,030 --> 00:07:17,270
I still can't believe
I couldn't convince him

161
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:18,270
to stay put here.

162
00:07:18,270 --> 00:07:20,180
Where did Kenshin go, Grandpa?

163
00:07:20,180 --> 00:07:22,010
And when's he coming back here?

164
00:07:22,010 --> 00:07:27,010
Well, I hope he'll be
back with us very soon.

165
00:07:27,010 --> 00:07:28,210
Me, too.

166
00:07:28,210 --> 00:07:34,050
♪

167
00:07:34,050 --> 00:07:35,220
I still need to talk with Okubo

168
00:07:35,220 --> 00:07:37,060
and ask him if killing Shishio

169
00:07:37,060 --> 00:07:39,160
would really mean
peace for everyone.

170
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:42,070
I know from the candid way
he spoke when he visited

171
00:07:42,070 --> 00:07:43,250
he'll give me an honest answer.

172
00:07:43,250 --> 00:08:09,250
♪

173
00:08:09,250 --> 00:08:11,070
Will this day never end?

174
00:08:11,070 --> 00:08:13,280
My meeting with the county
administrator may take hours.

175
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:15,210
After that I still
need to travel to Ito

176
00:08:15,210 --> 00:08:18,290
and meet with Himura
to hear his decision.

177
00:08:18,290 --> 00:08:21,200
There's only one answer
that's acceptable from him.

178
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:23,160
He has to do it no matter what.

179
00:08:27,110 --> 00:08:29,270
He simply must say yes.

180
00:08:29,270 --> 00:08:31,290
Without him we're
really done for.

181
00:08:31,290 --> 00:08:32,200
You know something?

182
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:34,150
You worry too much.

183
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:35,180
Okubo, why concern yourself

184
00:08:35,180 --> 00:08:37,210
with what might
happen in the future?

185
00:08:37,210 --> 00:08:40,290
Besides, you're
going to be dead.

186
00:08:40,290 --> 00:08:42,280
Shishio wanted me
to tell you this.

187
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:43,240
Now listen.

188
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:45,060
Enlisting Himura's a good idea,

189
00:08:45,060 --> 00:08:46,020
but it won't stop me

190
00:08:46,020 --> 00:08:47,210
from taking over the country.

191
00:08:47,210 --> 00:08:49,090
He wanted you to know.

192
00:08:49,090 --> 00:08:51,120
Too bad for you he's
not here to bail you out.

193
00:08:51,120 --> 00:09:00,280
♪

194
00:09:00,280 --> 00:09:01,270
Hold your horses!

195
00:09:01,270 --> 00:09:02,140
Huh?

196
00:09:02,140 --> 00:09:03,110
Whoa!

197
00:09:03,110 --> 00:09:04,140
Stop, you're being commandeered

198
00:09:04,140 --> 00:09:05,240
by Ito radicals.

199
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:07,130
Come out now, Okubo.

200
00:09:07,130 --> 00:09:08,190
We're coming in after ya!

201
00:09:08,190 --> 00:09:11,060
(shouting)

202
00:09:11,060 --> 00:09:12,220
The coachman's dead!

203
00:09:12,220 --> 00:09:14,110
(cheering)

204
00:09:14,110 --> 00:09:18,020
You can't hide, Okubo.

205
00:09:19,210 --> 00:09:20,200
Dammit!

206
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:22,150
Someone's assassinated him.

207
00:09:22,150 --> 00:09:23,280
Who would have done this?

208
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:25,070
That's not our concern.

209
00:09:25,070 --> 00:09:27,130
The question is what
are we going to do now?

210
00:09:27,130 --> 00:09:29,120
This really messes things up.

211
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:31,050
I say we pretend
that we're responsible

212
00:09:31,050 --> 00:09:32,130
for what just happened.

213
00:09:32,130 --> 00:09:33,100
Are you sure?

214
00:09:33,100 --> 00:09:35,130
It helps our cause.

215
00:09:35,130 --> 00:09:36,080
Agreed?

216
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,230
That sounds right, Shimada.

217
00:09:37,230 --> 00:09:39,110
Count me in.

218
00:09:39,110 --> 00:09:40,110
Agreed!

219
00:09:40,110 --> 00:09:41,090
We're all in!

220
00:09:41,090 --> 00:09:44,080
(laughing and cheering)

221
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,461
♪

222
00:09:48,170 --> 00:09:50,060
Sir Okubo murdered?

223
00:09:50,060 --> 00:09:52,190
Who would have killed
our Home Minister?

224
00:09:52,190 --> 00:09:53,280
Everybody get back.

225
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:57,060
Stand back, I said back.

226
00:09:57,060 --> 00:10:02,070
(gasps)

227
00:10:02,070 --> 00:10:04,250
It's Okubo.

228
00:10:04,250 --> 00:10:05,270
The same thing
could happen to you

229
00:10:05,270 --> 00:10:08,200
if you try to stop
Shishio, buddy.

230
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:10,160
I'd think twice before
you try anything.

231
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:19,010
♪

232
00:10:19,010 --> 00:10:21,100
Shishio.

233
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:23,160
He's responsible.

234
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:34,250
♪

235
00:10:37,250 --> 00:10:39,080
Extra, extra.

236
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:41,120
Home Minister assassinated.

237
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:43,010
Read all about it.

238
00:10:43,010 --> 00:10:45,230
All provinces mourn
murdered statesman.

239
00:10:45,230 --> 00:10:47,040
Are they kidding?

240
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:49,120
Just who else could they mean?

241
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:53,240
Read this, it seems
Okubo's been murdered.

242
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:55,240
"Earlier today in Akasaka,

243
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:58,080
our country lost a
renowned statesman.

244
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:59,120
A man considered by many

245
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:01,220
to be the central pillar
of the Meiji government

246
00:11:01,220 --> 00:11:03,180
has been assassinated.

247
00:11:03,180 --> 00:11:07,040
Toshimichi Okubo is dead".

248
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:15,250
♪

249
00:11:15,250 --> 00:11:18,060
This is the way
Shishio does things.

250
00:11:18,060 --> 00:11:19,080
He takes the truth,

251
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:20,170
which is that he was responsible

252
00:11:20,170 --> 00:11:22,070
for Sir Okubo's untimely death,

253
00:11:22,070 --> 00:11:23,190
and he distorts the facts

254
00:11:23,190 --> 00:11:24,240
so that the people
of our country

255
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:26,030
think this heinous act

256
00:11:26,030 --> 00:11:27,190
was committed by
some other group.

257
00:11:27,190 --> 00:11:28,200
He keeps out of sight,

258
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:30,060
but he kills our
greatest statesman

259
00:11:30,060 --> 00:11:32,030
and keeps slicing
away at the fabric

260
00:11:32,030 --> 00:11:35,130
that holds our fragile
country together.

261
00:11:35,130 --> 00:11:38,070
It can't be.

262
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:39,080
(knocking)

263
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:41,170
I hope I'm not interrupting.

264
00:11:41,170 --> 00:11:43,000
Welcome, Yamayoshi.

265
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:45,100
You were the last one
to talk with Sir Okubo.

266
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:46,260
Please tell us about it.

267
00:11:46,260 --> 00:11:49,000
I met with him just before
he left in his carriage

268
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:51,070
heading to Akasaka and
he seemed very tired.

269
00:11:51,070 --> 00:11:53,170
The enormous pressure he
was under was getting to him.

270
00:11:53,170 --> 00:11:55,030
I mean, he was doing his best

271
00:11:55,030 --> 00:11:57,130
to keep our government afloat.

272
00:11:57,130 --> 00:11:59,020
It's been ten years
since the restoration

273
00:11:59,020 --> 00:12:00,130
and we have been so busy

274
00:12:00,130 --> 00:12:03,080
trying to suppress internal
strife and organize things

275
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:05,190
that we have very little
to show for all our work,

276
00:12:05,190 --> 00:12:06,280
it's disheartening.

277
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:09,260
The real restoration will
take place in the next 15 years

278
00:12:09,260 --> 00:12:11,250
and the only way we
will achieve our dream

279
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:14,210
is to win the people over
to our way of thinking.

280
00:12:14,210 --> 00:12:17,100
Without the common
man we are lost.

281
00:12:17,100 --> 00:12:18,180
Now it's time to expand

282
00:12:18,180 --> 00:12:20,160
and by beginning to
deal with domestic issues

283
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:21,150
the people will see

284
00:12:21,150 --> 00:12:24,020
we are worthy of their trust.

285
00:12:24,020 --> 00:12:26,110
I only wish I
were a younger man.

286
00:12:26,110 --> 00:12:27,200
Then I'd feel sure I'd be here

287
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:30,110
to see my ideas implemented.

288
00:12:30,110 --> 00:12:31,290
I know you can do it.

289
00:12:31,290 --> 00:12:33,240
You have my confidence, Sir.

290
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:35,120
The only way the
restoration will work

291
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,290
is to enlist the people.

292
00:12:36,290 --> 00:12:38,110
By building a national unity

293
00:12:38,110 --> 00:12:40,030
and organizing
our nation's states

294
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:42,120
the people will join our cause.

295
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:44,040
Once the people find
they are a vital part

296
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:45,230
of the process of government,

297
00:12:45,230 --> 00:12:47,250
we can't help but succeed.

298
00:12:47,250 --> 00:12:49,110
When people feel empowered

299
00:12:49,110 --> 00:12:51,250
instead of thinking a handful
of men decide everything

300
00:12:51,250 --> 00:12:53,000
then we will have the chance,

301
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:56,050
the chance to be a
truly great nation.

302
00:12:56,050 --> 00:12:57,260
He was a man for the people.

303
00:12:57,260 --> 00:13:00,030
But he was just too idealistic.

304
00:13:00,030 --> 00:13:01,240
But he was right.

305
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:03,240
He was the only one
who could do it.

306
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:05,100
His ideas were right,

307
00:13:05,100 --> 00:13:07,130
now he's gone.

308
00:13:07,130 --> 00:13:08,250
One other thing.

309
00:13:08,250 --> 00:13:11,170
Sir Okubo was usually quiet
and reserved when we spoke.

310
00:13:11,170 --> 00:13:13,240
But when we spoke
yesterday he was passionate

311
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:15,130
in the way he
related his thoughts.

312
00:13:15,130 --> 00:13:17,250
It was almost as
if he somehow knew.

313
00:13:17,250 --> 00:13:20,160
It was as though he wanted
his philosophy and his ideas

314
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:22,190
to keep on living.

315
00:13:22,190 --> 00:13:24,260
I, for one, will
never forget the man.

316
00:13:24,260 --> 00:13:27,080
He was the greatest statesman
of our time and, maybe,

317
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:28,230
the greatest of all time.

318
00:13:28,230 --> 00:13:32,060
(crying)

319
00:13:32,060 --> 00:13:33,270
♪

320
00:13:33,270 --> 00:13:37,260
Kawaji certainly seemed to
take Okubo's death pretty hard.

321
00:13:37,260 --> 00:13:39,280
Sir Okubo was like
a father to him.

322
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:42,110
He taught Kawaji
everything he knows.

323
00:13:42,110 --> 00:13:43,220
But Kawaji isn't the only one

324
00:13:43,220 --> 00:13:45,230
that will be affected
by Okubo's death.

325
00:13:45,230 --> 00:13:47,220
Our entire country
will be in confusion.

326
00:13:47,220 --> 00:13:50,090
This could put the
restoration flat on its back.

327
00:13:50,090 --> 00:13:51,260
With all three of
the great statesmen

328
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:53,120
of the restoration dead now,

329
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:55,290
all we have left are
third rate politicians.

330
00:13:55,290 --> 00:13:57,080
And you know what that means.

331
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:58,240
Shishio was licking his chops.

332
00:13:58,240 --> 00:14:03,170
He won't let this
opportunity pass him by.

333
00:14:03,170 --> 00:14:06,070
Saito.

334
00:14:06,070 --> 00:14:08,050
Where are you going?

335
00:14:08,050 --> 00:14:11,040
What are you planning to do now?

336
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:12,240
There's only one thing to do.

337
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:14,000
Go to Ito and see to it

338
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,250
that Shishio gets stopped.

339
00:14:15,250 --> 00:14:17,250
See ya.

340
00:14:17,250 --> 00:14:23,200
♪

341
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:26,060
Sir Okubo murdered
by dissidents!

342
00:14:26,060 --> 00:14:28,200
Ishikawa Royalists
claim responsibility

343
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:30,080
for Home Minister's death!

344
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:31,140
What's gonna happen now?

345
00:14:31,140 --> 00:14:35,230
(crowd talking)

346
00:14:35,230 --> 00:14:37,190
It's like the turmoil
of the Tokugawa era

347
00:14:37,190 --> 00:14:39,240
is starting again.

348
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:41,200
What have we done
to deserve this?

349
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:45,040
They should hang those
dissident bastards.

350
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:46,090
How can Uta allow this

351
00:14:46,090 --> 00:14:48,110
to happen to us?

352
00:14:48,110 --> 00:14:51,020
War might break out
among the rival factions.

353
00:14:51,020 --> 00:14:53,120
When is Sir Okubo's funeral?

354
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:55,200
No one will ever be
able to replace him.

355
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:57,190
Once the people feel
they are a vital part

356
00:14:57,190 --> 00:14:59,140
of the process of government,

357
00:14:59,140 --> 00:15:02,120
we can't help but succeed.

358
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:03,170
We don't want your opinion.

359
00:15:03,170 --> 00:15:04,180
He could save our country.

360
00:15:04,180 --> 00:15:06,000
Shut your mouth.

361
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,200
Shishio is licking his chops.

362
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:10,100
He won't let this
opportunity pass him by.

363
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:12,080
I see, the only
viewpoint that's valid here

364
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:14,140
is your own corrupt
government's viewpoint.

365
00:15:14,140 --> 00:15:16,070
I would rather be executed

366
00:15:16,070 --> 00:15:18,200
than go along with
your blackmail scheme.

367
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:20,230
I don't know much about
your Meiji government,

368
00:15:20,230 --> 00:15:22,220
but I have figured
out one thing.

369
00:15:22,220 --> 00:15:24,280
If the situation was
just a little different

370
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:27,050
you might be hiring
us to kill Kenshin.

371
00:15:27,050 --> 00:15:31,240
We will not allow Kenshin to
go to Ito and risk being killed.

372
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:33,160
Battosai, I told you.

373
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:35,000
The real you is a slasher

374
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,270
and will always be a slasher.

375
00:15:36,270 --> 00:15:38,180
A slasher cannot
be anything else

376
00:15:38,180 --> 00:15:40,140
until someone kills him.

377
00:15:40,140 --> 00:15:41,290
The only time
you're really alive

378
00:15:41,290 --> 00:15:43,090
is when you're fighting.

379
00:15:43,090 --> 00:15:44,150
Or killing people.

380
00:15:44,150 --> 00:15:47,000
Deep down you know
what I say is the truth.

381
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:49,100
Your bloodthirsty hands
cannot let go of the sword,

382
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:51,150
no matter how much
you try to fight it.

383
00:15:51,150 --> 00:15:53,210
You should give
in to your destiny.

384
00:15:53,210 --> 00:15:56,180
(laughing)

385
00:15:56,180 --> 00:15:58,030
I know he's right.

386
00:15:58,030 --> 00:16:00,210
The slasher still
lives in my heart.

387
00:16:00,210 --> 00:16:02,020
I've been trying
to get rid of him,

388
00:16:02,020 --> 00:16:04,160
but maybe that's not possible.

389
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:07,030
I really tried to do
what I think is right,

390
00:16:07,030 --> 00:16:09,120
but maybe what's right
is being true to myself

391
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:13,070
instead of fighting the part
of me that lives as Battosai.

392
00:16:13,070 --> 00:16:14,260
To find out who I really am

393
00:16:14,260 --> 00:16:17,280
I must confront my own fear.

394
00:16:17,280 --> 00:16:20,270
The only way to know which
Kenshin is the real me

395
00:16:20,270 --> 00:16:23,140
is to give Battosai a
chance to live again.

396
00:16:23,140 --> 00:16:27,240
Then I can choose which
life is best for me.

397
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:41,220
♪

398
00:16:41,220 --> 00:16:42,280
Oh, isn't it just my luck

399
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:44,100
to get an emergency patient

400
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:46,050
on a night like this?

401
00:16:46,050 --> 00:16:49,030
Come on, Grandpa
said we need to hurry.

402
00:16:49,030 --> 00:16:50,170
I was hoping to
stay here tonight

403
00:16:50,170 --> 00:16:53,210
and see if Kenshin
decides to come home.

404
00:16:53,210 --> 00:16:56,140
Well, I sure can't allow
Dr. Fox and two little girls

405
00:16:56,140 --> 00:16:58,100
to walk home alone at night.

406
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:01,010
Come on, ladies.

407
00:17:01,010 --> 00:17:03,100
That sounded
awfully patronizing.

408
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:05,040
Kaoru, if Kenshin
comes back while I'm gone

409
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:07,020
you can tell him
where my sake jug is.

410
00:17:07,020 --> 00:17:08,030
Okay.

411
00:17:08,030 --> 00:17:09,090
And be careful.

412
00:17:09,090 --> 00:17:10,280
We'll be careful and quiet.

413
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:12,070
Sh, quiet!

414
00:17:16,150 --> 00:17:18,080
Kenshin.

415
00:17:18,080 --> 00:17:20,080
Aw, come on, Kaoru.

416
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:22,150
You know that he's probably
gonna come back here.

417
00:17:22,150 --> 00:17:23,190
I know it's not nice to say,

418
00:17:23,190 --> 00:17:24,250
but since Okubo's dead

419
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:26,160
there's no reason
for him to go to Ito.

420
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:29,100
He'll come back home.

421
00:17:29,100 --> 00:17:32,000
Then I'll run down the
road and welcome him home.

422
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:36,020
Hey, Kaoru.

423
00:17:36,020 --> 00:17:38,200
Nice move, Yoshi boy.

424
00:17:59,130 --> 00:18:02,010
Maybe I shouldn't
get my hopes up.

425
00:18:02,010 --> 00:18:04,190
Maybe he decided to
start wandering again.

426
00:18:13,020 --> 00:18:15,090
Those fireflies
really are beautiful.

427
00:18:15,090 --> 00:18:16,040
Kenshin!

428
00:18:21,150 --> 00:18:24,190
♪

429
00:18:24,190 --> 00:18:26,160
What is it?

430
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:28,230
Sir Okubo was
assassinated yesterday.

431
00:18:28,230 --> 00:18:30,190
I know, we heard.

432
00:18:30,190 --> 00:18:32,060
I'm pretty sure about one thing.

433
00:18:32,060 --> 00:18:34,270
Shishio and his gang did this.

434
00:18:34,270 --> 00:18:36,050
I couldn't live myself

435
00:18:36,050 --> 00:18:41,120
if I let Shishio
get away with this.

436
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:42,280
That's why I came to tell you

437
00:18:42,280 --> 00:18:45,070
I have to go to Ito.

438
00:18:45,070 --> 00:18:47,270
Kaoru, did you hear what I said?

439
00:18:47,270 --> 00:18:48,190
Kaoru?

440
00:18:48,190 --> 00:18:51,090
Ito?

441
00:18:51,090 --> 00:18:53,030
I have to ask.

442
00:18:53,030 --> 00:18:56,230
Are you going back to
being the old Kenshin again?

443
00:18:56,230 --> 00:19:00,270
I wish I knew.

444
00:19:00,270 --> 00:19:02,100
It's been a long time.

445
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:04,270
But when I was fighting
Saito I had a strange feeling.

446
00:19:04,270 --> 00:19:08,010
I could feel the old
warrior Battosai coming back.

447
00:19:08,010 --> 00:19:09,190
There's still a
slasher inside me

448
00:19:09,190 --> 00:19:11,190
and he's fighting to get out.

449
00:19:11,190 --> 00:19:13,190
Battosai still lives
somewhere inside me

450
00:19:13,190 --> 00:19:15,160
and he just won't
allow me to ignore him.

451
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:17,130
I must give him a
chance to live again.

452
00:19:17,130 --> 00:19:18,080
But it's not fair.

453
00:19:18,080 --> 00:19:19,110
Your life's so much better

454
00:19:19,110 --> 00:19:20,260
without that killer
running your life.

455
00:19:20,260 --> 00:19:22,230
Can't you see I want
what's best for you?

456
00:19:22,230 --> 00:19:24,260
The one you shouldn't
give up on is Kenshin.

457
00:19:24,260 --> 00:19:27,270
At least we know he's good.

458
00:19:27,270 --> 00:19:29,050
If I stay here any longer

459
00:19:29,050 --> 00:19:31,290
than you'll all be
pulled into this mess.

460
00:19:31,290 --> 00:19:34,020
The best thing I can do
is let Battosai out again

461
00:19:34,020 --> 00:19:35,270
and see what happens.

462
00:19:35,270 --> 00:19:44,080
♪

463
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:47,030
I'll never forget the
first time that I met you.

464
00:19:47,030 --> 00:19:48,130
And I remember you told me then

465
00:19:48,130 --> 00:19:50,230
that you didn't care
about my past, Kaoru.

466
00:19:50,230 --> 00:19:51,230
That made me very happy

467
00:19:51,230 --> 00:19:55,180
and I knew I found a new home.

468
00:19:55,180 --> 00:19:57,140
You've been great.

469
00:20:01,150 --> 00:20:02,230
I've had so much peace,

470
00:20:02,230 --> 00:20:04,050
so many fun filled days

471
00:20:04,050 --> 00:20:06,090
being part of this
wonderful family,

472
00:20:06,090 --> 00:20:08,050
feeling the love we all share.

473
00:20:08,050 --> 00:20:18,250
♪

474
00:20:18,250 --> 00:20:20,020
Thank you, Kaoru.

475
00:20:20,020 --> 00:20:22,120
Thank you for
everything you've given me.

476
00:20:22,120 --> 00:20:26,240
♪

477
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:30,150
I just have to go to Ito.

478
00:20:30,150 --> 00:20:33,150
But that doesn't mean
that I don't love you.

479
00:20:33,150 --> 00:20:35,150
Goodbye, Kaoru.

480
00:20:35,150 --> 00:20:39,130
(crying)

481
00:20:39,130 --> 00:21:07,080
♪

482
00:21:07,080 --> 00:21:11,230
Oh, Kenshin.

483
00:21:35,772 --> 00:21:51,280
♪

484
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:53,050
♪ (singing in Japanese) ♪

485
00:21:53,050 --> 00:23:08,180
♪

486
00:23:09,120 --> 00:23:11,250
♪

